[SN]TITLE[SN]
River Teviot search for bag with 'dangerous' flare

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police officers are trying to find a missing bag containing a rescue flare which they say could be "dangerous" in the wrong hands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The bag went missing from a a car park by the River Teviot - known locally as the Spetch - near Newton St Boswells on Thursday at about 17:00.
It belonged to a kayaker, who had left it underneath a car, and also contained some clothing and a whistle.
Police Scotland asked anyone with information to call 101.
Inspector Keith Dougal said: "This bag contains a flare which could be dangerous if it is discharged in an enclosed area. As such we are particularly keen to retrieve the bag and return it to its owner."
